caption: Our favorite spot in Huntsville! Service and food is consistently fantastic!
We had reservations for 130 brunch. They were pointless. May as well not bother. Not going to be honored by the manager.
A downtown huntsville staple that always delivers

My wife and I visit here on special occasions, as this place has some of the best food in town. The prices are reasonable given the caliber of food, and they never cease to amaze with the quality! The staff is super friendly! Perfect for a date night, anniversary, small gathering of friends.

Party of 5 for Sunday brunch today was very disappointing. I had shrimp and grits but shrimp were too rubbery to eat. 2 of us had fried green tomato benedict:  the poached eggs were hard boiled, no hollandaise sauce and the tomatoes were cold. No sweet tea at a Southern cuisine resturant?? The only thing worse than the food was the service. All 5 of us left still hungry and thirsty.

Ate here for the first time with my wife and daughter. Daughter recommened as she frequents regularly. I had the fried chicken club sandwich with fries and it was pretty good. Wife had the shrimp street tacos with fried green tomatoes and she loved them. Was a nice day that you could sit outside & enjoy a good meal and the weather. Would recommend and might try it again when we come back for another doctor appt
Get the pancakes 😍

Heads up! There is NO socially distanced dining, it is a very small place and you enter to a small room with a bar full of non-mask wearing patrons. (-1) We were unaware as we were just passing through and parking was difficult. It was Saturday brunch. Server (William) was nice. (+1) Chef was unaccommodating, but food was good. (-1/+1) Coffee was terrible :( (-1) I would give them another shot for dinner, but we live in Birmingham and were there on business. There were tons of eateries and coffee shops so I was a little disappointed with our choice.

My wife and I love this restaurant. Its our favorite go-to date night restaurant, and every dish is great in its own right. Klaire has always been our server and she is consistently wonderful, and Im sure the rest of the staff are equally as terrific.
Great dining experience! Everything was top shelf!
I love commerce kitchen! They play really great music and have healthy lunches. I like to go here when I'm in a hurry, and also when I take a client to lunch. They never disappoint!

So we tried this place cause my son was working close by so we met up and had lunch it was nice the place is real small the pimento cheese isn’t good but my son had fish and chips he got 2 fish 2 shrimp ?! Haha kinda crazy idk or where the shrimp came in  but he said it was good I got the wedge salad and it was really good atmosphere was nice server was nice we gonna go back and try dinner oh and another good thing they take reservations so try it
Food was great, felt very safe and distanced from other diners! The espresso martini was the hit of my meal!
Had dinner delivered. Shrimp and grits were not good at all. Shrimp was tough and tasted old. Made the whole dish tast bad. Was unable to eat. Waist of money tonight.
The food is fantastic, service is polite and professional. My favorite so far is the fried green tomato BLT. I’m from NM and loved the breakfast tacos!

Delicious Christmas dinner! Their set Christmas menu provided enough variety to keep a family of four happy. The cocktails were made to perfection, too. The wait staff was friendly, and they worked together to get the family's food out at the same time without requiring huge trays. Great teamwork!

A more down-to-Earth, Southern style of sorta fine dining.  I always love everything that comes out of the kitchen, and their cocktails are a treat if you're in the mood.  It's overall a more home-like, welcoming version of Cotton Row.

if i could give less than 1 star i would.  Why ? Because they messed up my reservation and had us seated outside in December.  As a result, we didnt have a table and they offered to have us wait 2 hrs . No thanks. Fortunately we found an amazing Tex Mex place on Winchester Rd . called El Mariachie, nothing to look at but the food was excellent.

We brought an out of town guest with us for our first time visit here.  The appetizers (fried green tomatoes and crab cakes) and entrees (seafood, poultry and prime rib) were all excellent.  Service was great as well.
The food was fantastic.  Bloody Mary's made just like you want them. Waitress was polite and knew all the answers.
Wonderful food. The service left a bit to be desired. Our server forgot about us for awhile.
Had a lovely chat with the bartender, stayed for dinner when we planned on just having a drink, then enjoyed the prime rib! Very delicious! Enjoyed the staff and the food. Great vibe!

Exceptional. One of the best dinners overall my husband and I have had in a long time. He had the ribeye and said it was the best he’s had - the sauce it comes with was super good but it honestly didn’t need it, it was tender and flavorful by itself! I had the blackened Mahi-mahi and grits. The grist were creamy and paired perfectly with the fish. Also don’t be afraid to get dessert! It’s completely worth it. The creme brûlée was perfect and was great with their coffee cocktails.
We really enjoyed the food.  I loved the shrimp & grits.  Hubby had the pork chop...he liked it also.  Their Cosmopolitan was spot on 👍🏻 Service was good.  Will definitely go back.
Food is always great, staff is very polite. They can get busy and service slows down but its worth the wait.
Closing time shows 10 PM it is 8:54 PM right now and I just called them they told me that they have closed SMH.
Wonderful food and drinks. Top notch service.

The food, drinks and service are good must of the time. This would be a 5 star review if the food and drinks were consistent. Sometimes your drink is great, sometimes not so much. Sometimes your steak is seasoned, the next time is not. If they were consistent in their greatness, this would be a go to every week.
The Fried Green Tomato Benedict was delicious and original, accompanied by impecable service. Very recommended!

Great place for Southern soul food in a chic farm to table setting. This is hands down my favorite restaurant in downtown Huntsville and is perfect from appetizer to dessert. The place is a bit pricey, but it's worth it for a special occasion or when you feel like it's time to "treat yourself."

My friend took me to lunch here. First time to eat here. We both had the fish tacos with jalapeno slaw and fried green tomatoes. They were perfect! My friend didn't care for the taste of her tortillas,but I loved them. The whole dish was a taste sensation that I had never experienced but hope to again! The wait staff was attentive but not bothersome. Highly recommended.
Food was delicious, service was great!

Crab cakes were terrible and crazy salty. My salad leaves literally had mud on then so they don't wash lettuce. Very over priced for what you get. Not impressed at all.  Tried to come back and they can’t be bothered to make a chicken sandwich at 4:02??? 2 minutes past their “cut off” what a joke of a place.
Bomb fired green tomatoes

Food and service were excellent. Daily special of grilled Grouper was delicious however a little small. My wife had shrimp 'n grits which were great as usual. Dinner for two reasonably priced. Server was superb - very pleasant and attentive.
Solid food. I was expecting more from the "special" drinks.
Commerce Kitchen's steak with espresso sauce is my favorite steak in the city! They also have great drink choices and appetizers
Great meal, great service, wonderful outdoor seating.

Amazing place to eat with eclectic atmosphere. The perfect example of downtown Huntsville ambiance. The outdoor seating under the trees is beautiful. The steaks are the best in town with a great wine and delicious cocktail list. You will have a fabulous time at Commerce.

Service was great. Red snapper was chewy and not good. Prime Rib was good. The seasonal pasta with short rib was good very heavy green pepper flavor.  I expected more summer vegetables with it but it was still ok. My daughter had the Ahi Tuna Salad and she loved it.
Small portions and slow service
Amazing food and service!!!
The one star is deserved due to them providing plates for the birthday cake. That's it. Screwed up our reservation and had us seated inside instead of outside. Food mediocre .
Excellent place.  Everything is great.
Great food, not much of a beer selection.
A perfect description of southern hospitality and delicious food.

Excellent atmosphere, clean historical and modern at the same time.  Fried Goat Cheese Salad and crab cakes were our starters and we ordered Coffee Crusted NYSTRIP and Shrimp & Grits.  All expertly timed and our waiter was attentive as well as excellent!  This is a GEM. Thank you for a good meal
Great food, great staff.
Fantastic Every Time!
Great service from Erica. Enjoyed our time there.

Great food and service. Nice interior, mostly quite. Classic restaurant and seating. Burger was cooked to order just right. Plenty of cheese. Street tacos. were tasty with a fried green tomato topper.

Me and my new wife were visiting Huntsville for our honeymoon and wanted to eat a nice meal while in town. We went to Commerce Kitchen because it looked nice. It was beautiful inside but the service was not exceptional. We sat there for 20 minutes before we were even given complimentary waters. We ended up just leaving and getting Jimmy John's 2 blocks down the street. We were not pleased with the service at Commerce Kitchen
Good food but I was still hungry! ☹️
Outstanding gourmet burgers. Burgers the way they are meant to be. Juicy, tasty, crunchy,n filling..  cannot believe you can get this in surat !!...
Excellent food and service! We always pick this place for date night or a special occasion and it’s always perfect!
A restaurant with very slow service, a very busy and noisy atmosphere, serving overpriced, mediocre food.
Great service! Good food!  Will go again!
Fried green tomato BLT sandwich with pimento cheese was incredible as well as the cornneal fried oysters. Obviously a foodie fave from the clientele I saw.
Great Menu Variety

Wonderful meal sitting outside. It is quaint and romantic. The Huntsville downtown dining and entertainment scene is growing in the right direction, and the Commerce Kitchen is a contributing factor. The staff are well trained as you would expect. The food and drink menu have interesting and delicious selections. However, it was the desert that blew us away. The Caramel Butter Cake is incredible. I would not hesitate to go back just for a cup of coffee and another serving of that desert.
Very delicious meal and quick service. Make sure to get a reservation before you go.
Probably a nicer place for a foodie, which I'm not.  But I can appreciate that I was eating at a higher level than normal.  Great staff and wonderful old building.
The food was amazing!
Food was good.  Service wasn't bad but a little slow.

Food was amazing. Restaurant is a little too loud to be intimate. Initially sat a small table with metal chairs which were not comfortable but asked to move to a booth and we were accommodated. Service was adequate but not amazing like the food was. The food was so delicious we will definitely be back.
Amazing food and the servers were AWESOME!

I’ve been wanting to try this place for a very long time. Unfortunately, I was not impressed. The tacos appetizer came out cold. We didn’t complain because we wasn’t sure if that was how it was supposed be. Plus the pork on the tacos was tough/dry. The shrimp and grits were good but they came out like warm. They were cold by the time I took my last couple of bites. The fried chicken was not good at all. The collard greens were good. The parmesan  fries were really good!  I probably should have complained about the tacos but my fiancé said, let be.
Very nice restaurant good atmosphere great food and most importantly awesome staff members I highly recommend for a date night.
Commerce Kitchen is one of the better lunch spots in town. Also, had Old Rip Van Winkle for outrageously good prices...

The food was high quality. Got the filet which was cooked perfectly. The shrimp and the sauce were done well. My waiter was polite and knew the menu, but too a while to come by the first time and also didn't get a refill when empty.
Had the people rib and it was excellent. One of the best i every had.

The fish tacos are good but the service is really slow. I'm also not a fan of the way they've got the table set up. You're so close to the people next to you you feel like you're in their conversation. Little awkward.
Great food, good service.
The brunch menu food was excellent and our server Chris is a wealth of knowledge and did a great job
Nice quiet little restaurant with great food and drinks.
Great food, nice ambience

Place is kind of small, so I do recommend making reservations. Food was great and service was great as well. My only knock was that my Old Fashioned seemed to be missing simple syrup, but I like bourbon on its own, so it wasn't a big deal at all.
The food and service was amazing. My husband and I ordered the fried green tomatoes,  shrimp and grits and he ordered a steak. We were very pleased and I cant wait to go back.

I arrived with a small group and we took over the bar. The wedge salad was spot on. We ordered several appetizers. The spicy chicken bites were by far the best. I ate more than I should have and forgot to order their gumbo... I’ll have to find my way back sometime to try it.  The bar has a small but impressive selection. I was schooled by someone who truly knows and enjoys bourbon that they have some of the best at some of the most reasonable prices in town. I would probably have given 4 stars but they get a bonus for not ripping people off.

Modern takes on classic Southern dishes. The food is delicious and they are pretty good at navigating dietary restrictions. Good wine and cocktail selection. Last time I was there I had a Chai Old Fashioned, and it was great. Only thing is the restaurant can be a little cold sometimes as the floor vents are always blowing, so dress appropriately. Sum up, this is well worth being over of your regular spots in town!
Great service! Great food!
It was ok shrimp and grits good but burger for 16 dollars a little high service good friendly staff.
We have eaten dinner here several times and always have great service and fantastic food. This one is local gem!
Nice atmosphere and great food. Reservations recommended.
Awesome food and service!
Great food and service
Great food and service
Great local joint with refreshing spins on classic comfort food dishes. Definitely worth a trip downtown for a quick bite
When can I go back to Huntsville and try more of this delicious food? Great ambiance and wait staff too!
A bartender that knows how to properly make cocktails and good food. Limited menu of spirits and food but what they have is nice. 👌
Reservation doesn't mean anything. 7:00 PM ... Hahaha and it's too late to try somewhere else
Great place in downtown Huntsville.  Super nice atmosphere that is relaxed yet polished.  Food is wonderful and bartender was awesome.

We had made reservations, when we got there it was so crowded. She put us at a high top table where all the people standing waiting. It was awful it was so loud. So we left...a romantic restaurant...I think not!!! I was so excited to go and I was very disappointed.

Loved the quaint yet classy atmosphere! Staff were genuinely kind and made sure coffee cups were always full! Food was astonishingly delicious! Prior to my visit I always thought a restaurant in Portland Oregon had the best Cornbeef Hash. Commerce Kitchen now holds that title in my mind! Will be returning again and again. ♡

A nice, fine dining experience. Our party of 20 was accommodated quickly and we were able to order and receive drinks quickly. All of them were a hit. And were well presented.  The waiter admitted to not being very helpful and had to run to look at the soup for the evening. It was a bit strange at a place that was serving $30+ plates.  The lamb chops were nice and tender but a bit boring. I made a mistake in not ordering the steaks as that looked like the winner of the night.  The desserts took the cake though. The cheesecake and bread pudding are necessary for after dinner. A nice stop in Huntsville for a nice night.
High quality food and drinks, with friendly staff, serving in a pleasant, intimate atmosphere.

Great options from the menu. Everything from Shrimp and Grits to Blackened Catfish. It was really good. Best to make a reservation. I had the fish tacos. The place is comfortable and inviting. The staff was very friendly. I will go again and take my wife instead of my coworkers.

Excellent food, friendly staff and a lovely view of the courthouse across the street in the evening. I had the Monday night pot roast special, my girlfriend enjoyed there seasonal pasta with shrimp and we split a Crème brûlée. While the food was delightful , we had gone to celebrate my birthday. Due to the restaurant being rather small and crowded, I would not recommend it for an intimate dinner. Perfect place though for a group of friends to grab a bite and enjoy a drink.
Good and drinks were excellent and the quiet quaint space is a welcomed social spot
Remarkable service and the vibe around the community gives off such a joyful feeling it makes you feel as if your a city man just sticking it to tv
Great service and good food
The food and cocktails were both right on point. Not be recommended for kids, but ours did ok. 😆
Shrimp and grits were amazing!
Great food and atmosphere!
Great dinner and dessert. Great dinner menu
Great Food

Limp, graying, overcooked vegetables, under-cooked pasta, over-salted everything (and I like salt).  Overpriced to boot.  Service was mediocre, I left one of the smallest tips I've left in a long time.  Pretentious without the quality to back it up.

Great place to take the family.  One of if not the best brunches in town!  Great wait staff and a couple of the best chefs in town!  If you have a special occasion and you dont wanna dress all the way up or break the bank this is the place to go! They have live music in the summer and very good drink specials. They also have a great wine selection since they are owned by the same Chef as Cotton Row James Boyce.  I ate here for my birthday this year and their special events coordinator Stephanie facilitated my supprise birthday wonderfully with my fiance by having her come in for a wine tasting and personally helped make the night better than I could have ever imagined! My fiance's dad and I had their Cowboy Ribeye topped with crab Bearnaise sauce served withTruffle Mashed Potatoes and a  Balsamic Honey Glazed Brussels Sprout and it was to die for!! My parents and her mother had their Pot Roast and it reminded them of my grandmother's which I had never heard them compair a restaurant to.  My fiance had their filet  mignon  topped  with king trumpet mushrooms served with heir corvair and truffle mashed potatoes with Bordelaise sauce I will definitely come back!!
The food was wonderful!  Appetizer service was prompt...entree service, not so much.  Have an old friend to catch up with?  Perfect.  On a schedule? Try Purveyor.
Just wasn't what we thought the hype was going to be
Very good food with good portions and value.  Excellent prime rib.
Just wasn't good drinks was to expensive
Best shrimp and grits ever!!
Southern food with flair
Great Sunday brunch with $5 bloody Mary bar.
It was great food and the staff was very friendly.
Great Southern food! The customer service was great as well.

Amazing worth every penny. The chicken was delicious. Cheese burger meal phenomenal and the fish was also amazing. Side of Collard greens was very tasty. It was like it came from someone's grandmothers kitchen. It was as beautifully plated as it was delicious. All around wonderful restaurant and staff. Portion sizes were small and left you wanting more, but enough to make you full. It was just so good I would have rather had a bottomless refill. However I would make myself sick if that were an option

I have heard good things about this restaurant, but recently went in for the first time. It is pricey for the area but the food was excellent. Staff was very friendly and helpful. Excellent selection of wine and craft cocktails. Food is elevated southern and the entire menu looks delicious. Even though it is southern, I was still able to find healthy options. I opted for the harissa salmon with rice and vegetables. Would be a great place for a work celebration or date night.
Had Taylor as a server ! Great Service and Food ! Definitely recommended !

Loved it! Gaood drinks, absolutely amazing food, and stunning desserts. We sat on the patio, which was comfortable and gorgeous. Everyone was nice and in good spirits. Highly recommend the coffee crusted NY strip; one of the best steaks I have ever had. Beef Tagliatelle was gorgeous, and the salmon was by far the best I have ever had. Perfect texture and temperature, with a wonderful crisp on the outside.  Serisouly, can't stress enough how great this place is. It's worth every penny.
The best restaurant in Huntsville

We started with the hot crab dip with pita chips which was very tasty.  For entrees, we ordered the shrimp skewers of the day, the roasted salmon and the new york strip. Everyone ate every bit of their meals! We even made sure to leave room for dessert! The creme brulee was excellent- loved the vanilla bean flavor!
Great food...great atmosphere
Our server was wonderful
Everything was wonderful!
Had the Thursday special of blackened catfish. Very good!
Really like this place.  Quaint downtown location.
Timely service and great food. Try the New York strip and the fried chicken bites.
Great food and service.

Food was good but overpriced for Huntsville. Atmosphere is very noisy and tables so close and our waitress had a terrible attitude as if we were a bother to her because we did not spend a great deal of money. Would not recommend or go there again very disappointing.

You will not be disappointed! Restaurant week  is is winding down and the area's focus is not lost on Commerce Kitchen. The food quality is matched only to the care and expert skill used in preparing & perfecting their recipes. Reservations for indoor dining is needed during the busy months while patio dining is on a first come basis. The soup of the day is always a creative treat. Try their shrimp and grits, fried green tomatoes and coffee crusted rib eye steak. Dessert?? Creme brulee... Yessss!
Great food and outdoor seating. Prompt service and tasty food. Was $27 a plate plus drinks and tip, but worth doing it every now and then.
The food was tasty and the service was very good. The dining area was clean. I don't have anything special to say about it. I would try it again if I'm in town.

Went to try chicken and waffle for subday brunch, it was just below basic and amount of chicken they served with waffle was literally a joke, less than wat any restaurant serve for kids menu tiny 2 1inch chicken strips , I dnt expect it for 15$ meal, this was kind of not up to the standards of a considerably fine restaurant. French toast was ok.
Ate there for restaurant week and it was very good! Shrimp and grits with fried green tomatoes and bread pudding. I ate it all. Yum!
The staff was very polite, friendly and helpful.  Interior clean, love the interior design.  Food was amazing

I can say I was whelmed. We started out each with different signature cocktails that were ok. We followed that up with the fried green tomatoes and pimento cheese and the Street Tacos. The Fried green tomatoes were under seasoned and the tacos were soaked in juice making them messy to handle or eat. My wife had the pork chop that was ok with what tasted to be microwave broccoli. I had the ribeye that was cooked very well but a poor cut of meat, losing 1/4 to gristle and fat. It was drowned in a bordelaise sitting on very watery garlic mashed potatoes ( to much sour cream at least). There was complimentary bread, if you asked for it. Again I was whelmed, nothing particularly bad but nothing standout either.
Great food as always....and services

Been to Commerce several times in the past and very disappointed in the meal I had tonight. Chef don’t put three day old snapper on the fish of the day menu and charge 28 bucks. Spent too much time on the coast to know better.

My wife and I met some friends for dinner at Commerce Kitchen in Huntsville, Alabama. This was my second visit to this great restaurant. The service was great and the food was delicious. My wife enjoyed the shrimp and grits and I enjoyed their burger with a fried egg on top. We finished our dinner with creme brulee.
I went for dessert and port. Beautiful, cozy, great service. The pecan pie was fantastic.

The staff work hard at this place, especially Kayla and Taylor, they're like a blur when the restaurant gets busy! Yet they somehow make you feel at home and catered to - a true talent. The food has been consistent but just hang out at the bar for some great cocktails, apps, and atmosphere and you wont be disappointed 😋
Awesome food and service in a small quaint setting. Will be back!!
Great food in historic downtown

My first encounter at Commerce Kitchen was about 6 years ago and I enjoyed the atmosphere and food!  Now, last night, the special, Mahi Mahi, was rubbery around the edges and luke warm as was the orzo and ratatouille! I would say flavorless as well. So I’m from New Jersey and have ate from Arkansas to Moscow.  This was disappointing and I don’t feel confident in the positive reviews posted on google. Oh and the music was terrible when a song or two finally played.  We were told internet connectivity issues. Hmm, Northern Alabama needs Verizon!!  P.S. Chris, our server, was very engaging.

Had a delightful lunch, as part of a party of 6. The food and service were both excellent! Enjoyed a yummy appetizer of fried green tomatoes, plus several entrees which were all quite tasty. And the desserts were divine!  We will definitely be returning here next time we're in Huntsville.
Good place for lunch. Haven't had dinner but based off lunch, I would expect quality.
Delicious brunch, coffee was fantastic and all the staff was very friendly and helpful

Love love love this place!  It's a fancy kitchen! Eat at the quaint bar in the bar or dine at a table in the adjacent room. Good for large parties with advance notice. We had a party of 7 and our salads were brought out pretty quick. Try the goat cheese salad (I still dream about that fried goat cheese patty) and the braised beef tagliatelle pasta.

Nice place, we went on a whim by reading other reviews. Service was friendly and warm. The food was really good. Perfect portions. Try the fried green tomatoes. I say give this place a two thumbs up..

One of our favorite places to go for date night. The atmosphere is upscale without being overly pretentious. The food is consistently amazing, as are the cocktails. The same award-winning chef as is behind Cotton Row (if I'm not mistaken), but the price is much more reasonable. I'd recommend a reservation.

Solid shrimp and grits and the pulled pork green tomato eggs Benedict was a good combination.  The crispy fried green tomato would have been perfect just as the bread.  The added English muffin was a bit too much.

I tried the fried green tomato sandwich with pimento cheese and it was heavenly. Four stars for the kitchen messing up the order the first time, and asking if we wanted it anyway- and the restaurant is so small people are actually yelling over one another.

Fantastic Americana southern comfort food in an upscale environment.  The patio seating is great with string lighting all around.  Great for a special occasion or just an average night out with someone special or group of friends.
Stopped in for a glass of wine and a snack. Very tasty, great service. Main dinning area was cute and cozy, definitely will be going back for dinner next time we're in Huntsville.
It was ok. I expected to be wowed from what I'd heard, but brunch was just ok. Probably would try it again to see if it was an off day.
Helpful & friendly staff, great food. The braised short-rib grilled cheese is a great lunch choice
(Translated by Google) Great cook mui riko  (Original) Genial cocinan mui riko
Had an absolutely lovely experience at Commerce Kitchen while with my friend for a afternoon lunch.  It was a beautiful day to sit outside.  We had excellent service and enjoyed our meal immensely.
Food was great! Had surf and turf and salad.
Have the redfish
The food/service was amazing! If I'm ever back in this area I'm coming back!
Great food
Seated quickly. Orders taken quickly. Drinks arrive quickly. Food arrives quickly.  Superb service and food. What more could you ask for?
Good variety menu with that southern twist. Friendly service and a great walkable area.

Commerce Kitchen is a good choice in Huntsville, AL. I ate there with four  other people while on a business trip. Two of us were traveling for business. We ate there on May 28, 2019.  Parking was easy since it was the weekday and after 5:30 PM. I found free street parking within 100 feet. The friendly staff greeted us as we entered. The restaurant is average size for a downtown establishment and they also had outdoor seating, though we sat inside. They seated the five of us in a booth and we did not feel crowded. I ordered the ribeye served over green beans and mashed potatoes. It was all good and I would order it again.  Overall, Commerce Kitchen did a really good job, the food was good, the staff friendly, and the atmosphere was conducive to a pleasant evening of discussion. I recommend this place.
My daughter and I had a wonderful time.   Our waitress was very friendly and polite.   The food was delicious!  I ordered the shrimp and grits and it was soo flavorful!

Terrible place to work. The owner doesn't care about his staff, only about profits. Frequently visits and helps other venture (Cotton Row) but only comes to Commerce to scream at the staff Ramsay style (without the skill).
Very good.

I love the chicken here. It is so fabulous. The service was good. I would eat here again. Plenty of parking is available around the place, but you can park in the parking garage. It's by a really cool hardware store. The vibe downtown Huntsville is worth checking out. Lots of variety several streets apart.
Killer burgers.
Amazing food!! Highly recommend the fried chicken bites for an appetizer and salmon for main course. Next time I am in Huntsville, I will be back!
Food not worth the price , red Robin has better burgers
Awesome southern lunch.
The food was amazing!! Great outside seating option.
Outstanding as always
I had the shrimp and grits and it was delicious. We were able to sit outside. Great atmosphere

Extremely unaccommodating staff, could not get a table despite having a reservation well in advance & had to wait. Finally when we got the table, it was minuscule & in the passage way of the restaurant where everyone walking past bustled into the table. Food wasn’t bad. Indifferent service
Great food and the manager Mike is fantastic...Chris is the best server I've ever had

I thought i would try something new as far as food and I don’t regret it. The appetizer i had was fried green tomatoes with pimento , they were very crisp which i like and thick but they were so under seasoned without the pimento on top. So I’ll probably never cop green tomatoes from any restaurant outside of southern restaurant.  Secondly i had the harissa salmon breakfast bowl with eggplant zucchini and salmon. Now that was seasoned it was so so good! I wished i was served a bigger portion as i am a woman who can eat; you see the random waffle. Yeah that’s mine too.  The waffle was so delicious though. Very sweet for a regular waffle which i enjoyed because i hate plain waffles.  The atmosphere was okay, it was kind of different and weird to be the only black person in the whole restaurant, and not even a worker to be seen with melanin. But it’s okay, these are just the times we are in. Good food none the less, just a little pricey. LOL.  follow my  page on Instagram @__getfitwithtj☺️
Good food, nice ambiance. My only issue was the vents along the baseboards meant my legs were frozen by the end of the meal. Not much you can do about that in an old building though.

Have gone to Sunday brunch a number of times and come away amazed and satisfied every time! Chef Jimmy Boyce succeeds at everything he puts his hand to. All three of his restaurants are fantastic. Service is traditional and professional, really old school and done right. Food is incredible and unique to this area and you will not be disappointed whatever you eat. I give this whole experience my highest praise, don't miss it!
Excellent food and service

Nice cozy place down town. On weekends gets a little busy so if you have a large group you might want to RSVP. That is if you dont want to wait a long time. The food was good I have the ribeye, sweet potato mash and collard greens. The serving size of the sides is a bit small for the price. The steak was really tender one of the best steaks I have had in a long time. I did not need any sauce just they way it came was great. Try one of the local beers, I had one forgot the name but it was an IPA and it was good. I will definitely have to go back to this spot as soon as possible!
Love this brunch find! Hubs got stuffed French toast and I got the fried green tomatoes to which we both split and loved! They have a make your own mimosa and bloody mary bar as well!

Commerce is one of our go-to’s for a nicer evening. The old fashioned is essential if you’re a bourbon fan. I pressed the issue since the restaurant was nearly empty, could you please make an exception to this "policy" and allow us to enjoy a meal in a booth? The waitress had been borderline annoyed from the start, but we stayed.  Our mistake.  It was 2:15 on a Sunday afternoon.  I had the Hangover burger.  It was excellent. We were both eager to order dessert.  The waitress had been borderline annoyed from the start, but we stayed.  My guest had creme brulee, while I ordered the Bourbon Milk Chocolate Pecan Pie.  Her dessert looked perfect, but was actually heated through, a fail for brulee.  My dessert came with the crust half missing off the back of the pie.  Backless may be seductive in a dress, but not so much with pie made in a frozen supermarket crust.  At $8 per slice, that's a $48 pie that didn't involve even making a crust.  Shame.  Shame.  The waitress didn't apologize for the piece being messed up in serving.  She also didn't inquire when it went untouched.  My guest was served brulee with a fork.  We couldn't even find our server for 10 mins.  I finally got up, found another server to get a freaking spoon.  No apologies.  No courtesies.  The check came and the waitress ignored the untouched botched dessert, but charged for it.  Save yourself the trip.  You can botch food at home without the markup and the disrespect.

Update: Went back for brunch for a family member's birthday. It did not change my opinion. I ordered a meal of sides. I understood going in that each side was $4 a piece, which is fine (I do not mind paying for quality and who messes up breakfast right?). I ordered a waffle, which was delicious, a side of fruit and bacon (to split). I received 3 pieces of bacon (regular bacon). The fruit was two slices of oranges (no bigger than 1/8" each), three strawberries, and three blackberries. The fruit was unwashed and one of the blackberries was rotten. AGAIN I don't mind spending money, but that seems ridiculously overpriced to me. My husband got chicken and waffles. It had sat for so long before being served that the crust of the chicken stuck to the waffle and came off and was flavorless.The coffee was really thick, which is fine, but it had so many grounds in it that I seemed like you had to chew the coffee. We try to always give restaurants the benefit of the doubt because we know how hard the industry is, but we are disappointed.  We were celebrating and thought Commerce Kitchen would be a wonderful place. It seems to have rave reviews. We got right in and the restaurant was clean, unique decor (great decor), and the staff was dressed nicely. We ordered drinks and an appetizer which were incredible. Then things went downhill. The main course was disgusting. I ordered steak (my favorite). It was way overcooked, the sauce made it taste like airplane food, and I subbed my green beans out for fries (which they served me the fries and green beans but not the mashed potatoes). The fries left a lot to be desired. My husband got his favorite meal of lamb. It was all fat, the bones were shredded into the meat. The best part of his meal was the kale. On top of that, it was very pricey. I don't mind spending money on a good meal, but this was not that. #disappointed
